Package com.github.yeetmanlord.reflection_api

Class NMSObjectReflection

java.lang.Object
com.github.yeetmanlord.reflection_api.NMSObjectReflection
Direct Known Subclasses:
NMSAxisAlignedBBReflection, NMSBlockPositionReflection, NMSChatComponentTextReflection, NMSDataWatcherReflection, NMSEntityReflection, NMSItemStackReflection, NMSNBTBase, NMSNBTTagCompoundReflection, NMSNetworkManagerReflection, NMSPacketReflection, NMSPlayerConnectionReflection, NMSPlayerInteractManagerReflection, NMSScoreboardTeamReflection, NMSServerReflection, NMSVec3DReflection, NMSWorldServerReflection
public class NMSObjectReflection extends Object
Implementation Note:
If you were to ever extend this class and create mappings for it, I recommend following this rule:
    You should have a public static field called `staticClass` which is the NMS class that object refers to. This is for mappings testing.
    In general, it's also good practice since it makes code more concise.

      public NMSObjectReflection(Object bukkitObject, String methodName)
      Will create a reflection based getting the nms equivalent of a Bukkit object Despite bukkitObject being an object it still must be an actual Bukkit object with the method being the method to get the nms equivalent
      Parameters:
      bukkitObject - A Bukkit object that you can get an NMS equivalent with a method
      methodName - The name of the method to get an NMS equivalent of a Bukkit object

    • invokeMethodForNmsObject

      public Object invokeMethodForNmsObject(String methodName, @Nonnull Class<?>[] argsClasses, @Nonnull Object[] args) throws NoSuchMethodException
      Runs a method and returns the return value of that method If the method is a void method will return null
      Parameters:
      methodName - The method to invoke
      argsClasses - The classes of the arguments in the method in order.
      args - The actual arguments for the method in order.
      Returns:
      The output of the method or null if it is a void method
      Throws:
      NoSuchMethodException - This exception is thrown when the given method name does not exist
      API Note:
      I do not believe that you can use this method to run final methods because to my tests it does not work
